M.I Abaga is ready to do what he did in 2008 with his debut album, Talk About It. He takes a cue from Kanye West, who he says stole his idea of releasing albums consecutively. The three albums he mentions are: Check out his tweet below: We are closing the HipHop conversation for the year in August! 3 Albums Executive Produced by The Greatest Rapper in Africa @MI_Abaga August 17 – Crown by Loose Kaynon x AQ August 24 – Yung Denzl by MI Abaga August 31 – BadBoyBlaq by Blaqbonez Case Closed! pic.twitter.com/m0rQ0CjHK4 — Chocolate City Music (@choccitymusic) July 25, 2018 